#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/shop.rst:119
msgid "Discount tags"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/shop.rst:121
msgid "Discount tags are specific barcodes used to apply a percentage discount to a product. They follow a specific discount nomenclature that allows the POS to recognize the barcode as a price reduction rather than a new product. These are commonly used for items nearing their :doc:`expiration date </applications/inventory_and_mrp/inventory/product_management/product_tracking/expiration_dates>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/shop.rst:127
msgid "A carton of milk is expiring tomorrow. By scanning a barcode following the discount nomenclature (e.g., a barcode starting with `2250`), Odoo automatically applies the defined price reduction of 50% to the milk during the current transaction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/shop.rst:132
msgid "Barcode nomenclature"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/shop.rst:134
msgid "Barcode nomenclatures explain how barcodes are identified and classified. When a barcode is scanned, it is linked to the first rule that matches its pattern. This pattern syntax adheres to a standardized method of prefix matching; a barcode is considered a match if its prefix aligns with the pattern."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/shop.rst:139
msgid "Patterns also define how numerical values —such as weight, price, or percentage— are encoded into the barcode. These are indicated by `{NNN}`, where the `N`'s define the position of the digits."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/shop.rst:142
msgid "To view or edit these rules, go to the :ref:`POS settings <pos/use/settings>`, scroll to the :guilabel:`Inventory` section, and click the :icon:`oi-arrow-right` (:guilabel:`Internal Link`) icon next to :guilabel:`Barcode Nomenclature`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/shop.rst:146
msgid "For discount tags, use the :guilabel:`Discount Barcodes` rule. The default pattern is :guilabel:`22{NN}`, meaning the barcode must start with `22`, followed by two digits representing the discount percentage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/shop.rst:None
msgid "discount tags nomenclature setting form"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/shop.rst:155
msgid "To allow for three-digit discounts (such as `100%`), add an extra `N` to the :guilabel:`Barcode Pattern` field (e.g., `22{NNN}`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/shop.rst:159
msgid ":doc:`/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/barcode_nomenclature`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/shop.rst:164
msgid "To use discount tags, scan the product barcode or manually add it to the cart. Then, scan the discount tag. The discount is automatically applied to the last product added to the cart."
msgstr ""

