#: ../../content/applications/sales/rental.rst:60
msgid "A bike rental company offers the following rental prices for its electric bikes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/rental.rst:62
msgid "1 day: $100"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/rental.rst:63
msgid "3 days: $250"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/rental.rst:64
msgid "1 week: $500"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/rental.rst:66
msgid "A customer wants to rent this product for eight days. What price will they pay?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/rental.rst:68
msgid "After the order is created, Odoo chooses the second line because it is the lowest price. The customer pays three times the '3 days' rate to cover eight days, totaling $750."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/rental.rst:71
msgid "1~\\text{day} * 8 &= 8~\\text{days} \\\\\n"
"3~\\text{days} + 3~\\text{days} + 3~\\text{days} &= 9~\\text{days} \\\\\n"
"1~\\text{week} + 1~\\text{week} &= 14~\\text{days} \\\\\n"
"\\\\\n"
"100 * 8 &= $800 \\\\\n"
"250 + 250 + 250 &= $750 \\\\\n"
"500 + 500 &= $1000\n"
"\n"
""
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/rental.rst:80
msgid "Therefore, the customer pays $750 for the eight-day rental period."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/rental.rst:85
msgid "Rental pricelist rules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/rental.rst:87
msgid "Extra rental prices are configured in the product's :guilabel:`Prices` tab. The prices are configured like advanced :doc:`pricelists <sales/products_prices/prices/pricing>`, where the following fields work as conditions for the price to be applied:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/rental.rst:91
msgid ":guilabel:`Pricelist`: The pricelist for which the pricelist rule is valid."
